        "comment": "Up to 2300 m rain will fall from late morning in some regions. This situation will give rise to significant moistening of the snowpack at low and intermediate altitudes. <br/> <br/> Below approximately 2300 m and on very steep slopes small to medium-sized wet snow slides and avalanches are possible as a consequence of the rain. <br/> In places where the snowfall level is higher the avalanche danger is greater. <br/> <br/> The conditions are unfavourable for ski touring, snowshoe hiking as well as off-piste descents, both due to the strong moistening of the snowpack at mid and low altitudes and due to locally poor visibility.",
